description:
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust are recruiting a Driver/Porter to work in their Decontamination Services Unit based in Enfield which opened in June 2019.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of the driver/porter is to assist in the reprocessing of medical devices required for clinical use by ensuring the timely delivery and collection from all Trust and external customers. You will be required to load and unload sterilisers, despatch surgical instruments and flexible endoscopes, load and unload trolley washers and other duties as specified in the job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The working pattern is 37.5 hours a week Monday to Friday 22:00 to 06:00. ( night shift).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful we require -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A clean driving license of C1 Category&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous driving experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good physical fitness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good customer service skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A flexible approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be a numeracy and literacy screening assessment on the day of the interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Stuart Tuffin&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Logistics Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: stuart.tuffin@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0207 794 0500 ext 36581&lt;/p&gt;
